British media entrepreneur Robert Maxwell, who publishes Britain's Daily Mirror, said Monday 
he is involved in negotiations to buy a U.S. newspaper worth "hundreds of millions of dollars." 
The newspaper was not identified but there is speculation that it might be The New York Daily 
News, which is struggling to restore profitability; USA Today, which would mesh with 
Maxwell's efforts for the new paper The European; or the Chicago Sun-Times that has been 
sliding in circulation since 1985.

Officials of each of these newspapers denied they were negotiating with Maxwell, who recently 
bought three US tabloids: the Globe, National Examiner, and the Sun.</SUM>

